verse_part: When ye do the office of a midwife
to him that did the wrong,
and it shall come to pass,
and when he took it out,
And it shall come to pass,
And it shall come to pass,
that they may hold a feast
and thou shalt be cut off
As soon as I am gone out
ye shall keep it a feast
And it shall come to pass,
And it shall come to pass,
so that they lent unto them
then thou shalt break his neck:
and I will get me honour
when I have gotten me honour
and I will prepare him an habitation;
them that rose up against thee:
And it shall come to pass,
And thou shalt set bounds unto
then shall he let her be redeemed:
were wont to push with his horn
and it shall come to pass,
the first of thy ripe fruits,
then I will be an enemy
and I will cut them off.
and thou shalt drive them out
and as it were the body
and [so] it shall be joined together.
when thou hast made an atonement
and according to the drink offering thereof,
he shall burn incense upon it.
he shall burn incense upon it,
to minister in the priest's office,
when he had made an end
and that I may consume them:
And it shall come to pass,
and take us for thine inheritance.
then shalt thou break his neck.
and he gave them in commandment
to minister in the priest's office.
and they caused it to be
made after the fashion of almonds
to minister in the priest's office.
the things that are to be set in order upon it;
